- VSCode Version: 1.8.1
- OS Version: OS X El Capitan 10.11.6

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Paste following code into the editor
`
file_get_contents('localfile.txt'); // shown in color
// $doc = new DOMDocument();
// libxml_use_internal_errors(true);

// $doc->loadHTML('<?xml encoding="utf-8"?>'.file_get_contents('dietlast.com.html'), LIBXML_NOBLANKS | LIBXML_NOCDATA | LIBXML_NOWARNING | LIBXML_ERR_WARNING);

// just black text is rendered from here onwards
file_get_contents('localfile.txt');
`
<img width="1180" alt="screenshot" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/18568258/21778331/00af3132-d6c9-11e6-82f3-780fbd094a79.png">


Comments are also behaving weirdly. For eg.
comment this line with shortcut [cmd | ctrl]+/
`// $doc->loadHTML('<?xml encoding="utf-8"?>'.file_get_contents('localfile.html'), LIBXML_NOBLANKS | LIBXML_NOCDATA | LIBXML_NOWARNING | LIBXML_ERR_WARNING);`

now try commenting the next line with [cmd | ctrl]+/, instead of php's comments, html comments are applied.
<img width="1180" alt="shot" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/18568258/21779369/618cd47e-d6cd-11e6-84a0-1db4e7a26dda.png">

- VSCode Version: 1.8.1
- OS Version: Windows 10

**Steps to Reproduce:**

1. In `a.ts`, export a function type:
```typescript
export interface MyFunctionType {
    (): string;
}
```
2. In `b.ts`, import the type and export a variable which implements it
```typescript
import {MyFunctionType} from "./a";
export function MyFunction: MyFunctionType = () => {
    return "test";
}
```
3. In `c.ts`, import the function variable, and invoke it
```typescript
import {MyFunction} from "./b";
MyFunction();
```
4. Place the caret somewhere inside the function call and *Go to Definition*.

**Outcome**
VSC takes you to `a.ts` (where the type of the variable is defined), not `b.ts` (where the variable is defined).

**Real life example**
You have a Knockout view model class with properties of type `KnockoutObservable<T>` (which may be invoked as a function). When you try to navigate to the definition of such a property, VSC takes you to the definition of `KnockoutObservable` in `knockout.d.ts`, not to the view model class.
